item.title: AP Statistics Exam
item.dc:creator: @jc22493 Jc22493
item.description:
@jc22493 wrote:

Si Force:

Is that like a general knowledge test where they examine you on all areas? In Ireland we have a test like that except it’s called a DAT test.

We take a classed named ‘AP Statistics’, which is a college course that can be taken in high school if requirements are met. In the beginning of May, we take a country-wide AP exam for the subject, and if we pass, we receive college credit for the class so we don’t have to take it again in college.
